`Graphics::setLights` is wired to `Direct3d11_LightManager::setLights` [Direct3d11.cpp:1067](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:1067). In `setLights`, the snapshot fields are filled only under `if (psSlot)`: world direction, diffuse, specular, tangent-minus-diffuse, tangent-minus-back, back, tangent, then `valid=true` [Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:176](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:176), [Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:187](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:187), [Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:190](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:190), [Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:194](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:194), [Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:196](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:196).

VS slot 0 maps `lightData[28]` to c16-c43 and `extendedLightData[8]` to c60-c67 [Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.h:219](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.h:219), [Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.h:221](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.h:221). `composeSlot0Shadow()` always writes ambient c16 from `d3.ambient`, but only writes c40-c43 and c60-c63 inside `if (d3.valid)` [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:376](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:376), [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:380](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:380), [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:382](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:382), [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:405](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:405), [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:410](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:410).

PS `SwgVertexConstants` b0 is 25 float4 registers / 400 bytes, with `PSCR_dot3LightDirection=c0`, diffuse `c1`, specular `c2`, tangent-minus-diffuse `c3`, tangent-minus-back `c4` [Direct3d11_LegacyPSConstants.h:54](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_LegacyPSConstants.h:54), [Direct3d11_LegacyPSConstants.h:68](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_LegacyPSConstants.h:68). The reflected PS variable names are generic `packedRegister0..4`, so the D3D11 code writes by register offset, not by semantic name [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:917](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:917), [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:1119](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:1119). Exact mapping: `packedRegister1` = c1 diffuse, `packedRegister3` = c3 tangent-minus-diffuse, `packedRegister4` = c4 tangent-minus-back [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:954](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:954), [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:956](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:956), [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:957](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:957). Those writes are also gated by `if (d3.valid)` [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:945](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:945).

**D3D9 Chain**

`Direct3d9Namespace::setLights()` forwards to `Direct3d9_LightManager::setLights()` [Direct3d9.cpp:3622](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9.cpp:3622), [Direct3d9.cpp:3629](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9.cpp:3629). `setLights()` stores the list and marks lighting dirty [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:310](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:310), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:312](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:312). Per draw, `Direct3d9::drawPrimitive()` calls `Direct3d9_LightManager::selectLights()` before drawing [Direct3d9.cpp:4012](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9.cpp:4012).

D3D9 selects a `T_parallel` into `parallelSpecular[0]` by specular intensity, then into `parallel[0..]` by diffuse intensity [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:423](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:423), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:427](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:427), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:434](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:434). If selected lights changed it calls `applyLights_vertexShader()`, otherwise it still calls `applyLights_vertexShader_dot3()` [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:500](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:500), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:503](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:503).

With a selected `parallelSpecular[0]`, D3D9 fills c40-c43 from object-local camera, object-local light direction, diffuse, specular [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:567](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:567), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:573](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:573), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:581](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:581), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:583](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:583), then uploads all `LightData` at `VSCR_lightData=c16` [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:723](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:723), [Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:28](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:28). It fills hemispheric back/tangent/deltas via `_vsps_setExtendedLightData()` [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:588](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:588), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:732](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:732), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:739](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:739), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:747](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:747), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:756](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:756), then uploads `ExtendedLightData` at c60 [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:725](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:725), [Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:45](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:45).

For the PS, D3D9’s `PixelDot3Data` layout is localDirection, diffuseColor, specularColor, tangentMinusDiffuseColor, tangentMinusBackColor [Direct3d9_LightManager.h:151](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.h:151). It uploads that block starting at `PSCR_dot3LightDirection` [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:592](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:592), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:601](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:601), with enum order c0-c4 [Direct3d9_PixelShaderConstantRegisters.h:23](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_PixelShaderConstantRegisters.h:23).

**Important Correction**

The source does **not** support the claim that D3D9 writes nonzero dot3 direction/back/tangent constants for a truly empty selected light list. In `applyLights_vertexShader()`, if `parallelSpecular[0]` is null, D3D9 zeroes `PixelDot3Data` and uploads it starting at c0 [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:610](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:610), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:614](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:614), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:624](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:624). Since `LightData` and `ExtendedLightData` were zero-initialized before the loop, the final c16-c43 and c60-c67 upload is also zero except ambient/alpha side fields [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:530](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:530), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:532](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:532), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:723](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:723), [Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:725](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:725).

`containsPrecalculatedVertexLighting()` only drives full ambient routing in D3D9: the shader effect reads the precalc bool from IFF [ShaderEffect.cpp:149](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderEffect.cpp:149), `StaticShaderTemplate` returns it from the effect [StaticShaderTemplate.cpp:229](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/StaticShaderTemplate.cpp:229), D3D9 stores it as `m_fullAmbient` [Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:776](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:776), and applies it via `setFullAmbientOn()` [Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:955](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:955). That sets `ms_fullAmbient` to `(1,1,1,0)` or zero [Direct3d9_LightManager.h:201](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d9/src/win32/Direct3d9_LightManager.h:201). It does not populate dot3 c40-c43 or c60-c63.

**Exact D3D11 Missing Write**

For the black D3D11 batch, the missing writes are the `d3.valid`-gated writes of:

`PS b0 c1/c3/c4` (`packedRegister1/3/4`) in `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData::apply()` [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:945](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:945), [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:954](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:954), [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:956](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:956), [Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:957](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:957).

`VS slot0 c40-c43` dot3 and `c60-c63` extended/hemispheric in `composeSlot0Shadow()` [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:382](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:382), [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:405](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:405), [Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:410](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:410).

But source-level comparison says: if the selected light list is truly empty, D3D9 also zeros these dot3 paths. So the actionable divergence is not “D3D9 has a hidden precalc dot3 source”; it is that D3D11 is receiving/using an empty or zero-dot3 light snapshot for that batch, while D3D9 must be getting a non-empty selected `parallelSpecular[0]` for the corresponding draw, or the “empty dynamic list” premise is not source-accurate.
